  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dba \u0d85\u0dad\u0dca\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb \u0d9c\u0dad\u0dca \u0d86\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba \u0d94\u0db6 \u0daf\u0dd4\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0daf?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Did you see how the protesters took over the Prime Minister's office?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The group protesting in Malpara, Colombo, demanding the resignation of the Acting President and Prime Minister, Ranil Wickremesinghe, entered the Prime Minister's office premises and are still there.",
        "Meanwhile, protests were held in front of the Speaker's official residence and the Sri Lanka Television Corporation located on Parliament Avenue in Battaramulla and the police fired tear gas and water cannons at the protesters several times to disperse the crowd.",
        "Another large group of protestors are still staying in the premises of the President's Secretariat, the presidential palace in the fort, as well as in the Aralia Gaha Mandir."
      ],
